-------------------------------------------------------------
compilation
-------------------------------------------------------------

By default all of the makefiles will produce an executable called
`mass2_v025'.  This can be changed by setting the `TARGET' macro on
the command line.  Some suggested `TARGET's are shown below. Currently
the following platforms are supported

    IRIX:   

        make -f makefile [DEBUG=-g [-O]] 
      
        Compile on mack or erebus

    DEC OSF/1:      

        make -f makefile.dec [DEBUG=-g [-O]] [TARGET=mass2_v025.dec]

        Compile on tophet.  Can run on both OSF/1 and Linux alpha.

    Linux i386:     

        make -f makefile.linux [DEBUG=-g] [TARGET=mass2_v025.linux]

        This is for the Absoft Pro Fortran 90 compiler.  This is
        installed on minos. 

    Linux alpha:    

        make -f makefile.dec NETCDFDIR=/usr F90=fort [DEBUG=-g [-O]] [TARGET=mass2_v025.axplinux]

        This uses the DEC Fortran 90 compiler for Linux.  This is
        installed only on gehenna. 

    Windows:        

        nmake /f mass2_v025.mak  "CFG=mass2_v025 - Win32 Release"
        nmake /f mass2_v025.mak  "CFG=mass2_v025 - Win32 Debug"

        Compile on r101243.